720870f-a.text:
Scene on Lenox Avenue looking north from 134th Street in the heart of the Negro Colony, New York City.. Many of the buildings are owned and practically all are tenamted by colored residents.
1921 Paul Thompson, photographer
N.g. ~ LS04
